Excellent fun, I had to tear myself away in the end! The gameplay is close to a mashup of Shadow Sarrior and Serious Sam, and for what I'm guessing is a pretty indie studio it has a good amount of polish. There's a strong sense that the design knows where it's going. 

Only two actual maps atm, though loot and spawns randomise variously. The devs seem pretty active too.

@Devs - great work with the sword blocking, best I've seen so far in VR. Other than the obvious that I'm sure you're working on, please could look into adding more "weight" to sword strikes on npcs (Improve hit anims, destructable models, ragdoll, etc.) Best of luck!
